properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 10 at 3:48AM PST until January 10 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the High Surf Advisory, large breaking waves of 20
to 24 feet expected in the surf zone. For the Coastal Flood
Advisory, minor coastal flooding expected.

* WHERE...North Coast and Central Coast.

* WHEN...For the High Surf Advisory, from 6 AM to 6 PM PST
Saturday. For the Coastal Flood Advisory, from 9 AM this
morning to 3 PM PST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only
isolated road closures expected. Dangerous swimming and
surfing conditions and localized beach erosion.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of high astronomical tide,
strong onshore winds and low pressure may result in minor tidal
overflow, especially in Aberdeen. High tide at Aberdeen is
around 11:36 AM PST at 11.4 feet. The tidal anomaly is 1 to 1.5
feet. High water levels in the Chehalis River will contribute to
minor flooding in Aberdeen.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area producing localized beach erosion.
